The paper focuses on 3D object detection using image and LiDAR data, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) categories. The paper also proposes a network architecture that involves adaptive fusion of features, which could be related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of region proposal networks, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL) but can also be applied to computer vision.
